io, Matteo, Sal, Carmelo, Concetta, Francesco, Gaetano, Gaspare, Gino, Rosario.","English: nickname, perhaps for a stubborn person, from Middle English <i>mule</i>, <i>muel</i>, <i>meul</i>, <i>moile</i> ‘mule’ (Old French <i>mule</i>). See also   Moyle   and   Moule  , with which this name may have been interchangeable.","French: nickname from <i>mule</i> ‘female mule’."]},{"name":"Milne","meanings":["Scottish (mainly Aberdeenshire and Angus): occupational name from Middle English <i>milne</i> ‘mill’, also found as <i>mulne</i> in south and western England and <i>melne</i> in southeastern England. The Scottish name has been established in Ireland since the early 18th century, and has absorbed some cases of Irish   Moyle  . Compare   Mill   1."]},{"name":"Moyles","meanings":["English: variant of   Moyle  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","English: in Devon and Cornwall probably a variant of   Mullis  .","Irish (Mayo and Meath): variant of   Miles  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Moyle was born in 1391, in Bodmin, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. She married William Benalva about 1450. She died in February 1482, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 91."},"et":{"1391–February 1482":"1391–veebruar 1482","1386–1452":"1386–1452","–Male":"Surnud","1420–1472":"1420–1472","1425–Male":"1425–Surnud","1391–1482":"1391–1482","1425":"1425","February 1482":"veebruar 1482","1420":"1420","about 1425":"umbes 1425","1452":"1452","1386":"1386","1472":"1472","about 1420":"umbes 1420","1482":"1482","1391":"1391","about 1450":"umbes 1450","Helston, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Helston, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Bodmin, Cornwall, England":"Bodmin, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1391–February 1482":"1391–helmikuu 1482","1386–1452":"1386–1452","–Male":"Kuollut","1420–1472":"1420–1472","1425–Male":"1425–Kuollut","1391–1482":"1391–1482","1425":"1425","February 1482":"helmikuu 1482","1420":"1420","about 1425":"noin 1425","1452":"1452","1386":"1386","1472":"1472","about 1420":"noin 1420","1482":"1482","1391":"1391","about 1450":"noin 1450","Helston, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Helston, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Bodmin, Cornwall, England":"Bodmin, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1391–February 1482":"1391–février 1482","1386–1452":"1386–1452","–Male":"Décédé","1420–1472":"1420–1472","1425–Male":"1425–Décédé","1391–1482":"1391–1482","1425":"1425","February 1482":"février 1482","1420":"1420","about 1425":"environ 1425","1452":"1452","1386":"1386","1472":"1472","about 1420":"environ 1420","1482":"1482","1391":"1391","about 1450":"environ 1450","Helston, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Helston, Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cornwall, England":"Cornouailles, Angleterre","Bodmin, Cornwall, England":"Bodmin, Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cornwall, England, United King